  "text": "In conclusion, the environment of PRs does not appear statistically different from that of normal galaxies. The number of fields surveyed in this paper is not large, but the result seems to be different from that reached for galaxies where interaction produces an observable nuclear activity, such as active galaxies or quasars [CITATION_1] , Heckman et al. 1985 , Hintzen et al. 1991 , Rafanelli et al. 1995 , whose environments appear possibly richer than that of the normal galaxies.",
